(104, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Applied Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The degree is limited to students with an Associate of Applied Science (AAS) degree. The Bachelor of Applied Science degree allows the transfer of an accredited (AAS) degree into a baccalaureate degree, counting the AAS credits much as credits in a major are counted.?', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(105, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Art in Fine Arts', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The B.F.A. in Art is considered the professional undergraduate degree in studio art and is designed to provide students with a thorough grounding in fundamental principles and techniques with opportunities for emphasis in one or more specific studio art areas.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(106, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Arts', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The BA in Art is a liberal arts degree that focuses on art in the context of a broad program of general studies.Students choose one of the following Areas of?Emphasis:?Studio Art, Studio Art with Minor, Art History with Minor, or Studio Art and Art History.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(107, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Arts in Psychology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'As a general Liberal Arts degree, Psychology majors develop excellent interpersonal research, writing, and analytical skills and are attractive to a wide variety of employers. Students may wish to take appropriate courses in other areas to enhance their skills and marketability. To prepare for a career in Psychology with a Bachelor??s degree, students are encouraged to consult with faculty to take appropriate courses and to pursue internships in the Billings community.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(108, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Biology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The degree imparts a foundation of information about botany, zoology, and ecology as well as molecular and cell biology and microbiology. It helps students Understand the basic principles and laws governing our world and have a global awareness of their discipline and demonstrate basic competency in laboratory, field and computer skills related to the sciences.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(109, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Biology in Medical Laboratory Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Bachelor of Biology in Medical Laboratory Science program is designed toUnderstand the basic principles and laws governing our world and have a global awareness of their discipline ,to Understand scientific methodology, and conduct scientific investigations using it.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(110, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Business Administration', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The BBA (General) is designed to provide students who do not wish to specialize in a specific area of business but instead would like to take a wider array of courses to provide a wide range in their management education. This program with concentrations in accounting, finance, economics, management, and marketing, offers graduates a background that is broadly applicable in today\'s job market. Further, Business Law and Ethics courses get students thinking about important topical and historical issues in the world of business. The business program prepares students with the conceptual and practical skills necessary for entry-level careers in the business field and advanced degree work. Classes, especially on the upper level, occur in a small setting that allows maximum individualized attention.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(111, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Business Administration in Accounting', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This degree helps students learn financial skills that are needed in the workplace. The program is geared for students that plan to take the CPA exam after graduation. In addition, many programs prepare you to receive your MBA after you complete your undergraduate studies. This way, you will have all of the credentials necessary to assist companies around the globe with their finances. Some programs are competitive, so there might be entrance requirements. It is important to check with the school you are interested in attending about eligibility. When the learners graduate, they will be qualified to work as an accountant for companies around the world. They will also be able to work in financial positions. They can specialize in tax or audit, depending on your skill set, background, and preference. Many students excel to great heights in this field. Some even become CFOs for companies.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(112, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Business Administration in Finance', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'From the Bachelor of Business Administration in Finance degree course, students will learn how money is raised and invested, how to manage a company\'s financial resources, and gain an understanding of capital markets, corporate finance, investments, and financial institutions. They can acquire the background to handle an array of financial challenges including the impact of interest rates, be able to perform risk analyses, know how to determine the value and return of investments, and grasp the regulatory environment. Students who graduate with a finance major are prepared to enter positions in corporations, financial institutions, brokerage firms, investment banks, and government. They also are prepared for post-graduate study in all areas of business.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(113, 15, NULL, NULL, 'USD 35', NULL, 'USD 20396', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Business Administration in Information Systems', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The university provides a Bachelor of Business Administration in Information Systems to the students. Undergraduate business students opting to pursue a BBA in Information Systems (IS) will gain a solid foundation in the design, use, and management of databases, enterprise systems, information security, and telecommunications technology. The IS program provides students with the background needed to give informational support for decision-making through business analytics and to understand complex project management initiatives. Graduates will be prepared for entry-level positions in the information systems field, either in user- or system-oriented departments. This program includes 120 credit hours and provides students with the background they need to give informational support for decision-making in organizations and to understand the impact that information systems have on the business enterprise.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(114, 15, NULL, NULL, 'CAD', NULL, 'CAD 11800', 'CAD', 'Bachelor of Communication Arts in Media Studies', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program is prepared to to examine the nature of the mass media through theoretical grounding and applied knowledge with a concentration in the construction and delivery of media messages and the effects of mediated messages and the structures and practices of the media industries on culture, society, politics, the economy, and individual attitudes and behavior.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
