(5204, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '15,200', 'EUR', 'Business and Social Sciences', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Formerly known as Business and Social Studies, this pathway will prepare you for your chosen undergraduate degree at the Strathclyde Business School or Faculty of Humanities & Social Sciences.\n\nYou will study three core modules that will focus on general skills useful in your chosen progression degree, plus route modules specific to your academic area.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5205, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '17,100', 'EUR', 'Engineering and Sciences', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'If you have dreams of studying a STEM subject at a UK university, theres no better first step than our preparation programme. Youll learn more about your chosen subject through our specialist modules, as well as developing your English language skills in a university setting  ensuring youre fully prepared to succeed at a UK university.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5206, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '15,000', 'EUR', 'Business Administration (BBA) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, '\n    Spend the first year of your BBA degree in a supportive and international environment\n    Learn from experts in international education\n    Study specialist English language classes designed to complement your academic studies\n    Gain necessary employability skills with our CareerAhead programme\n    Study modules focusing on the academic areas most useful to your degree\n    Progress to Strathclyde Business School, one of only 90 schools worldwide to be triple accredited\n', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5207, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '18,000', 'EUR', 'Civil Engineering', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This programme is equivalent to the second year of a Scottish undergraduate honours degree and has been designed in collaboration with the Faculty of Engineering at the University of Strathclyde. \n\nIn three-terms you will study specialist Civil Engineering modules, develop practical laboratory skills, and also benefit from academic classes to improve your English language and study skills.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5208, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '4,600', 'EUR', 'English Language Preparation (for Undergraduate Foundation Programme) - per term', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our English Language Preparation course will improve your English language skills up to the required level of IELTS 5.0 overall before you join the Undergraduate Foundation Programme.\nEnglish language entry requirements: \n\n1 term programme:\nAcademic IELTS for UKVI 4.5 overall (with minimum of 4.5 in writing)* \n\n*If you do not need a Student visa, or are exempted in another way, we can accept equivalent proof of English.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5209, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '11,650', 'EUR', 'Business and Social Sciences', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Formerly known as Business and Social Studies, this two-term pathway will prepare you for your chosen postgraduate degree at the Strathclyde Business School or Faculty of Humanities & Social Sciences.\n\nYou will study core modules, focusing on general skills and academic areas most useful to your chosen progression degree.  After you have successfully completed the Pre-Masters Programme and achieved the required grades, you can progress to Strathclyde in September.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5210, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, ' 11,900', 'EUR', 'Engineering and Sciences ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two-term pathway will prepare you for your chosen postgraduate degree at the Faculty of Engineering or Faculty of Science.\n\nYou will study core modules, focusing on general skills and academic areas most useful to your chosen progression degree. Upon achieving the required grades at the International Study Centre, you can progress to Strathclyde in September. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5211, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '9,500', 'EUR', '12 weeks', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'On a programme that is as efficient, extensive and easily accessible as the Online Accelerated Pre-Masters Programme, students are able to prepare for studying a Masters programme at the University of Strathclyde without relocating or leaving their lives behind. This provides great flexibility and stability, as you can get the most out of your education without the immediate cost of coming to study in the UK. \n\nOver one semester, this online programme will equip you with the academic skills, ability in business or finance and English language in preparation for your chosen postgraduate degree.\n\nIf you don\'t meet the English language requirement for the one semester Online Accelerated Pre-Masters Programme, then you have the option to study this programme either over two or three semesters, depending on your IELTS level. This will allow you to improve your language skills to a point where you are ready to study a postgraduate degree in the UK and communicate your points articulately in English, as well as prepare you for studying your degree subject by guiding you through specialist subject knowledge, skills and study techniques.\n\nBy design, the programme ensures that your teachers will be heavily involved in your studies, no matter where you are in the world, meaning that excellent academic and language tuition is assured.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5212, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '4,600', 'EUR', 'English for Pre-Masters (for 2 term Pre-Masters Programme) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our English Language Preparation course will improve your English language skills up to the required level of IELTS 5.0 overall before you join the Undergraduate Foundation Programme.\nEnglish language entry requirements: \n\n1 term programme:\nAcademic IELTS for UKVI 4.5 overall (with minimum of 4.5 in writing)* \n\n*If you do not need a Student visa, or are exempted in another way, we can accept equivalent proof of English.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5213, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, '2,750', 'EUR', 'Preparation for Study (for Accelerated Pre-Masters Programme)* ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our Preparation for Study course will improve your English language skills up to the required level of IELTS 6.0 before you join the 12 week Accelerated Pre-Masters Programme. Entry requirements are listed below:\nEnglish language entry requirements:\n\n5 week programme:\nAcademic IELTS for UKVI 5.5 overall (with minimum 5.5 in all areas)^', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5214, 102, NULL, NULL, 'NA', NULL, ' 4,500', 'EUR', 'Preparation for Study (for Accelerated Pre-Masters Programme)* ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our Preparation for Study course will improve your English language skills up to the required level of IELTS 6.0 before you join the 12 week Accelerated Pre-Masters Programme. Entry requirements are listed below:\nEnglish language entry requirements:\n\n5 week programme:\nAcademic IELTS for UKVI 5.5 overall (with minimum 5.5 in all areas)^\n\n10 week programme:\nAcademic IELTS for UKVI 5.0 overall (with minimum 5.0 in all areas)^', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5215, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'General Agriculture Certificate', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Spend a year putting theory into practice and earn a general agricultural certificate.\n\nFocus on either crop or livestock production. Whatever your choice, youll learn common skills for modern agricultural operations:\n\n    computer training\n    keeping accurate business records\n    using up-to-date technology for precision farming\n\nHalf of your time will be on college farm putting theory into practice. Student-Managed Farm  powered by New Holland includes:\n\n    beef and dairy herds\n    range land\n    crop land\n    facilities such as the [Dairy Learning Centre] and Agricultural Technology Centre\n\nOn the crop side youll learn practical field skills such as how to\n\n    identify weed and plants\n    assess pest problems\n\nOn the livestock side, develop basic production skills for dairy, cow-calf, and sheep.\n\nYoull likely want to stay another year. Earn a [crop technology] diploma or choose one of the animal science technology diploma majors.\n\n\n', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5216, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Agribusiness Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two year diploma program in Business Administration Diploma: Accounting Major will develop your technical accounting skills and expertise. The program will guide you in building industry connections and get real world experience between first and second year.\n\nDuring your first year youll build basic business skills. In your second youll take specialized courses in:\n\n-managerial and cost accounting\n\n-financial management\n\n-business law and statistics', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5217, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000 (18500 Livestock yr 1)', 'USD', 'Animal Science Technology Diploma (Beef, Dairy, Livestock Majors)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Hands-on and student-led experiences are the bedrock of this program. Students will grow both knowledge and skills related to:\n\n\nherd health\n\nnutrition\n\nanimal handling\n\nfinance\n\nmarketing\n\nThe Student-Managed Farm (SMF) powered by New Holland choices include purebred, commercial or livestock research units. Or, students may choose a student-led practicum.\n\n\nThrough labs and student-managed opportunities students will have a thorough and practical understanding of the beef industry. Students will be ready to start their career in any industry sector, or on their own farm or ranch.\n\n\nOnce graduated from this program, students may apply to one of the Bachelor of Agricultural Technology streams. This diploma can be used to complete the Bachelor of Agricultural Technology degree in two years instead of four. The second year of the animal science technology program includes two student-managed farm (SMF) courses.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5218, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Crop Technology Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two-year diploma program prepares you to learn agronomy, precision farming, sustainability and financial management. Students can Dig into both the science and business of the crop sector with our crop technology program. Best part would be they arent confined to classrooms. Youll also get your hands dirty on the Student-Managed Farm  powered by New Holland.\n\nTeamwork and collaboration are a big part of SMF experience. As part of the crop unit youll make real world decisions about:\n\n-what to grow on the college farm\n\n-managing production through to harvest\n\n-how to market and when to sell your corps\n\nAlong the way students will develop leadership and job skills. As a crop technology graduate, youre prepared to run your own farm or work in the retail agriculture sector.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5219, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Agriculture Sustainability Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year innovative diploma program bridges agricultural and environmental science. As well, it merges the concerns of both the public and producers. Consumers want to know where and how their food is grown. Farmers and ranchers care about conservation and productivity.\n\nThrough the program, youll be at the forefront of best practices and certified production.\n\nBest part is you will not be bounded only to the classrooms Youll spend time in field labs honing skills related to:\n\n-soil science\n\n-water management\n\n-grassland\n\n-livestock production\n\n-crop productions', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5220, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Agriculture Technology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year bachelor degree program in agricultur technology prepares you to take on the challenges of this rapidly evolving sector.\n\nIntegrating computer technologies and the Internet of Things has transformed agriculture. At Lakeland, you\'ll be immersed in those kinds of hands-on, real world experiences--experiences that bring together ag tech with production and business management.\n\nThe program bridges the gap between emerging technologies and ag production and management.\n\nGraduate with expertise and technical skills including: precision data systems, machinery learning, artificial intelligence and robotics.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5221, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Post-bachelor Commercial Agriculture Production Certificate', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The one year certificate program is designed for ag degree holders who want to build their practical skills.You\'ll boost both your real-world and critical-thinking skills by working and learning on our Student-Managed Farm - powered by New Holland. It\'s Canada\'s only student-managed farm.\n\nYou can choose crops or livestock stream. No matter your choice, youll gain insight and experience about typical agricultural production\n\nThrough the whole program you will be gaining knowledge on crops, livestock, equipment and technology.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5222, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Business Administration Diploma: Accounting Major', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two year diploma program in Business Administration Diploma: Accounting Major will develop your technical accounting skills and expertise. The program will guide you in building industry connections and get real world experience between first and second year.\n\nDuring your first year youll build basic business skills. In your second youll take specialized courses in:\n\n-managerial and cost accounting\n\n-financial management\n\n-business law and statistics', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5223, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '18500 yr 1 / 17000', 'USD', 'Business Administration Diploma: Real Estate Appraisal & Assessment Major', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two-year diploma program is designed to prepare you to become a highly versatile and in-demand professional in the property valuation.\n\nThis business admin diploma major starts with business basics. Then, youll dig into the core of your specialty with:\n\n-assessment principles\n\n-construction estimating\n\n-farmland evaluation\n\n-property analysis\n\n-computerized mass appraisal valuation of properties - it\'s now the industry standard\n\n\n', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5224, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Business Administration Diploma: General Major', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year General Bussiness diploma program provides you a broad range of business knowledge and skills. help you build business fundamentals and practical skills. Our expert instructors will ground you in accounting, organization behaviour, communication,s marketing and economics.\n\nThe program will help you in building industry connections during an optional 16-week summer practicum.\n\nYour elective courses give you flexibility to tailor your courses to your interest and goals. You even have the option to choose 2 courses from outside business. Youll discuss your goals and available courses with your academic advisor before you start second year', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5225, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Business Administration Diploma: Small Business & Entrepreneurship Major', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two-year diploma program in Business Administration Diploma: Small Business & Entrepreneurship Major develop a strong business foundation in accounting, marketing, finance, economics, human resources, information systems, and management.\n\nYoull start with business basics  accounting, communications and law. Then, focus on honing vital entrepreneurial skills such as:\n\n-salesmanship\n\n-leadership and supervision\n\n-small business management', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5226, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Business Administration Certficate: Administrative Professional', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The one year Business Administration Certficate: Administrative Professional certificate program is a professional program covers both the technical and interpersonal.\n\nIt provides you knowledge on bookkeeping, office procedures, computer applications, communications and human relations.\n\nBusiness basics in the 21st century also requires social media skills. Youll learn about specific social media platforms, as well as how to use them in a marketing plan. This course of one of two online ones in the program.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5227, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '32000', 'USD', 'Clinical Esthetician', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This one year program is designed to be qualified about the art of making someone feel great. You\'ll promote wellness as an important part of health care, use specialized skin care treatments, and address beauty, anti-aging and stress issues.\n\nYoull study the anatomy and physiology of the skin, diseases and pharmacology, epidemiology and nutrition. Plus youll develop communication and business skills in our 1 year Clinical Esthetician certificate program.\n\nYoull work with the latest technology: A multi-functional laser. Youll learn how to use it in the spa-classroom. Then, you\'ll practice your skills during public clinics in the student-led spa.\n\nClinical courses will be available to program alumni and other qualified estheticians.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5228, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Child & Youth Care Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two year diploma program will make you learn everything you need to know to support childrens critical development from infancy to school age in a childcare, educational or early intervention setting. The program will guide you about human development, health, safety and nutrition to support child development and how to create a creative and developmentally-appropriate curriculum and design a safe and inviting space for children.\n\nAdditionally it will prepare you for how to support children with exceptionalities and the business side of running a childcare practice.\n\nEach semester has a practicum. Your third practicum is unique to Lakeland. You and your classmates will set up and run a play program. Together, youll:\n\n-create a parent handbook\n\n-plan the activities, snacks and schedule\n\n-create a dynamic theme for the space', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5229, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Educational Assistant Certificate', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'In one year certificate program students will Support school-aged children on their educational journeys.In our educational assistant program, youll learn to work with children with different abilities, one-on-one and in small groups and in a variety of settings.\n\nThe program is designed to learn positive behaviour supports, human development, sensory development and how to support students with exceptionalities.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5230, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Environmental Sciences Certificate / Diploma: Applied Environmental Sciences', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This one year certificate/ diploma programe is designed to learn a wide range of environmental concepts related to water, soil and plants. You start in the classroom, but youll be in outdoor labs within your first month. You\'ll apply and practice what youve learned using real-life situations.\n\nWhen you graduate, youll be ready for environmental jobs across Canada.\n\nSome of the skills that you will be using during the courses are:\n\n-aquatic habitat assessments\n\n-wetlands & soil classification\n\n-water monitoring and sampling\n\n-environmental site assessment\n\n-plant identification', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5231, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Environmental Sciences Diploma: Conservation & Restoration Ecology Major', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'In this program students As a CARE graduate youll be making a difference for plants, soils, water and wildlife. Not just for now, but for future generations. Ecosystems and biodiversity are at the heart of conservation and restoration ecology (CARE).\n\nIn this two year program you will learn practical field skill.\n\nIn second year, youll focus on best management practices and stewardship techniques. Youll learn how to renew, restore and or conserve anything from grasslands to forest.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5232, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '17000', 'USD', 'Environmental Sciences Diploma: Environmental Conservation & Reclamation Major', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Through our Environmental Sciences Diploma: Environmental Conservation & Reclamation Major program youll gain skills and experience to ensure industry and the environment can coexist. This means either reclaiming disturbed lands or minimizing industrys effects on natural habitats.\n\nStudents will learn how to classify, manage and conserve soils, recognize and understand a variety of ecosystems, do detailed site assessments and apply reclamation regulations, guidelines and techniques to disturbed lands.\n\nStudents will visit and study forested, mined and cultivated lands as well as native and reclaimed areas.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5233, 91, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 90', NULL, '24200', 'USD', 'Esthetician Certificate ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The one year certificate program will give knowledge about anatomy and physiology of the skin, diseases and pharmacology and epidemiology and nutrition. Through the program you will master the science and art of making your clients look and feel their best as an esthetician.\n\nYou will be gaining knowledge at the campus on:\n\n-facials including chemical peel and microdermabrasion\n\n-manicures and pedicures including gel polish\n\n-body treatments such as wraps and scrubs\n\n-body waxing and more on\n\nYoull use specialized skin care treatments and address beauty, anti-aging and stress issues. Plus, youll develop communication and business skills as you help manage the student-managed spa. And most important, youll work with real clients to polish your skills.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5234, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$13,558.74 ', 'USD', 'Diploma-Archaeological & Cultural Resource Management Specialization', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program specialization emphasizes classroom and field-based learning in which students gain valuable applied research skills and experience in the growing field of archaeology and cultural resource management.\n\nThe Northwest region and First Nations communities provide the rich environment to learn about cultural heritage and interpretation, archaeological and cultural assessment, and how those fields apply to tourism, museums, and community cultural resource management', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5235, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$13,558.74 ', 'USD', 'Diploma-Sustainable Communities Specialization', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'With an Sustainable Communities SpecializationAssociate Degree, you can begin working with communities immediately or continue on to a Bachelor of Arts program at Simon Fraser University (SFU) or Royal Roads University (RRU).\n\nYou will be working at the leading edge of the biggest social, cultural and economic shift since the Industrial Revolution, helping communities, companies and nations grapple with the opportunities and threats of a rapidly changing world', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5236, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$13,558.74 ', 'USD', 'Criminology Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Associate of Arts  Criminology Specialization is a fully accredited, 2-year program that prepares graduates with a comprehensive grounding in criminology/criminal justice issues. \n\nThe program is the most flexible Criminology credential in that it maximizes transfer options to other institutions. Popular transfer option include:\n\n-Transfer into the third year of a university degree program to obtain a BA in Criminology (e.g. SFU, UFV)\n\n-Transfer into the third year of the Forensic Sciences program at BCIT to obtain a BTECH in Forensic Sciences\n\nTransfer options fully depend upon the elective courses chosen in the Criminology Diploma. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5237, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$13,509.27 ', 'USD', 'Business Administration Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two year Business Administration program gives you the credentials and expertise to get ahead in todays competitive workplace.Whether you want to work as an administrator in an office, pursue a specialized career in business and finance, or start your own company, CMTN offers one-year certificates or two-year diplomas that can help take you where you want to go.\n\nThe Business Administration program has concentrations in:\n\n-Accounting\n\n-Human Resources\n\n-General Management', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5238, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$12,226.38 ', 'USD', 'Post Degree Business Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year Post-Degree Business Diploma program allows you to support your existing education with a strong understanding of business practices.  Upon completing this two-year diploma, you will acquire skills appropriate for business managers and entrepreneurs. This program will be of particular interest if you are planning to manage or open a business focused on delivering a product or service related to your undergraduate education and experience.\n\nAfter graduation you can opt for Post-Degree Business Diploma program to expand your career into the world of business.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5239, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$13,905.03 ', 'USD', 'Applied Coastal Ecology Post Degree Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This one year program readies students for careers in coastal natural resources management, ecosystem restoration, environmental monitoring, and many others. ACE balances foundational learning in areas such as biology, geography, chemistry and oceanography with applied courses in areas such as salmon, ground fish and shellfish management, stream habitat restoration, rainforest ecology, wildlife management, and more.\n\nstudents get important technology training in computer database management, GIS mapping, surveying, technical writing, and presentation. Students participate in real-world, community-based projects to gain employment-ready experience and ultimately gain a strong sense of how coastal ecosystems react to the stresses imposed on them by human activity, and how to apply procedures to mitigate impacts and restore healthy ecosystems.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5240, 85, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 100', NULL, '$15,532.95 ', 'USD', 'Engineering Certificate', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program immerses you in extensive laboratory time, experiential learning opportunities, various group projects, and community-based learning. When suitable, projects are done in collaboration with community organizations and companies.\n\nIn British Columbia all colleges and universities have agreed upon a Common First-Year Engineering Curriculum (CFYEC). Completed in one year from September to June, our Engineering program covers the entire CFYEC curriculum. Upon completing the first year of an engineering degree at CMTN you can then transfer into the second year at the institution and program of your choice. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5241, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'Diploma (2-Year UG) -Business', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This program is general in nature and is designed to provide a wide choice of career opportunities in the business world. Students in the program will gain a practical understanding of key principles and practices necessary for success in the field of business, and acquire a range of fundamental skills in areas such as finance, accounting, human resources, operations management, marketing, and sales.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5242, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'Computer Systems Technician', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'In the CST program, students will acquire the expertise and practical skills to support the use of computers and networks within a business environment. Graduates are able to work both independently and as part a team to implement and maintain IT solutions to meet the day-to-day requirements of individuals and organizations. Over the course of the program, our students gain the specialized skills required for client/server computing, cloud computing, O/S virtualization, enterprise networks, administration and Internet management and more.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5243, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'General Arts & Science Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The General Arts & Science Diploma provides a broad liberal arts curriculum that prepares students for the workforce, college programs, or transfer to university. Core courses provide a solid foundation in communications and interpersonal skills, computers, mathematics, analytical skills, science, and general education. Courses are chosen in consultation with the program coordinator, ensuring the right mix to meet each students interests and vocational goals.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5244, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'Diploma (2-Year UG) - Hospitality', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This program prepares students to work in the exciting world of Hospitality, which includes a variety of topics  accommodations management, food and beverage management, specialized marketing, conferencing and banqueting, financial management and more. Our programs curriculum remains current through regular consultation with industry leaders, ensuring that your educational needs and future career expectations are being met and that you are job-ready when you graduate. Our instructors have extensive work experience in the industry and will help develop the essential skills required to be an effective supervisor, manager and leader in hospitality organizations locally, nationally and internationally.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5245, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'Diploma (2-Year UG) -Tourism', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This program will provide you with the opportunity to excel in the vibrant, rewarding and highly mobile tourism industry. The skills you acquire in this program reflect employer needs and will help ensure that you are ready for the work environment. Art and cultural tourism, hospitality and tourism law, sport tourism, special events planning and management, eco and adventure tourism, and historical tourism are but a few of the many subject areas that you will explore.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5246, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'International Business Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Globalization is the reality for any business. In the International Business Management post-grad program you will develop the knowledge, skills and attitudes to compete in the global business environment. In this program, students explore courses using real-life case studies covering over 120 topics.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5247, 81, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, '16200 CAD', 'CAD', 'Supply Chain Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The supply chain is one of the most essential sectors of the Canadian economy, involving about 767,000 workers from a range of occupations and industries. This graduate program builds on the students previous education and work experience and introduces all facets of supply chain management and logistics from a theoretical and practical perspective.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5248, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$40,693 ', 'USD', 'Associate of Arts Degree', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, ' This program provides a foundation in a range of academic disciplines, critical thinking, writing and research skills.In addition to required coursework in English, Science and Arts, you\'ll have the freedom to select from first- and second-year courses across every faculty at CapU.\n\nchoices can include everything from mathematics and computing science, to business, creative and performing arts, the social sciences or humanities.\n\nAfter completing associate\'s degree, you can ladder your credits into many bachelor\'s degree programs at CapU, including the Bachelor of Arts with a Major in Interdisciplinary Studies, the Bachelor of Arts with a Major in Psychology and many more. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5249, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$40,693 ', 'USD', 'Associate of Arts Degree  Creative Writing', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year program provides the guidance of practicing writers, who specialize in poetry and poetics (including digital poetics), the novel, micro-fiction, creative non-fiction, writing for children, ficto-criticism, radio and short film scripts.\n\nYou\'ll start you first year by studying multiple genres and branch out in second year to explore poetry, fiction, non-fiction, playwriting and writing for children.\n\nUpon graduation, you\'ll finish with an Associate Degree plus first- and second-year English and creative writing credits, which can be laddered in to one of the 15 bachelor\'s degrees at CapU. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5250, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$40,693 ', 'USD', 'Associate of Arts Degree  English', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program provides a comprehensive foundation of courses in the Arts and Sciences program with a literature specialization.This credential requires a total of 60 university credits with 18 credits in first- and second-year English.\n\nThe students will learn to demonstrate a breadth and depth of knowledge and skill appropriate to a student entering upper-division English courses.\n\nTo approach research problems and literary analysis with creative and critical thinking.\n\nStudents will be able Approach research problems and literary analysis with creative and critical thinking by using technology creatively and efficiently.\n\nStudents learn to demonstrate quantitative and qualitative reasoning and research methods', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5251, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$40,693 ', 'USD', 'Associate of Arts Degree  Psychology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program will make you learn the science, history and theories of Psychology and explore the fundamentals behind the science of human behaviour.Psychology is the scientific study of behaviour, thoughts, and feelings.\n\nIn the two-year Associate of Arts degree in Psychology at CapU, you\'ll explore topics including personality, motivation, and relationships.\n\nYou\'ll also examine how we develop and learn, how our social roles and culture affect us and the impact of stress and mental health issues.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5252, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$43,218 ', 'USD', 'Associate of Science Degree', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Associate of Science degree offers maximum flexibility, allowing you to take a broad range of science courses along with general electives. To understand and resolve most issues facing the world today, a foundation in the sciences is a strength.\n\nThe multidisciplinary and laboratory-intensive curriculum emphasizes both the academic and applied skill sets you need to succeed, particularly in the growing fields of green, health, and applied sciences.\n\nStudents can also ladder your credits into the upcoming Bachelor of Science (General) degree to continue your studies at CapU.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5253, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$43,218 ', 'USD', 'Associate of Science Degree  Biology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two-year associate\'s degree provides a firm foundation in the broad, exciting, and rapidly growing fields of life science.Biology is the science that explores and explains the life within and around us, investigating everything from how molecules move within cells to how ecosystems flourish in varied environments.\n\nThe multidisciplinary and lab-focused curriculum emphasizes both the academic and applied skill sets you need to pursue opportunities in a range of fields including health, biotechnology, and conservation and resource management\n\nAfter completing your degree, you can ladder your credits into the four-year Bachelor of Science degree at CapU, which will take its first students in Fall 2022. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5254, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$86,455 ', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Tourism Management Degree', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program will give you the business, management and communication skills to succeed in a competitive and changing industry.A degree in tourism management broadens your understanding of the global issues, impacts and challenges facing the tourism industry and prepares you to be effective in complex situations.\n\nCourses emphasize sustainability, community engagement, global consciousness and experiential learning with options to earn concentrations in hotel and resort management or adventure tourism.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5255, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$12,621 ', 'USD', 'Business Administration Certificate', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Program teaches students basic management skills that have practical value in a wide variety of jobs.The program requires successful completion of one required business course, two specialty business courses and a choice of three business elective courses (three-credits each) chosen from the School of Business course offerings.\n\nCredit from the certificate program can ladder into the Business Administration Diploma and/or the Bachelor of Business Administration.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5256, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$84,333 ', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Business Administration Degree', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The degree makes you to build a strong foundation in business knowledge, then continue with your general business degree  or develop in-depth expertise in your chosen area.The instructors bring up-to-date knowledge to the classroom, sharing the expertise that\'s made them successful. Small class sizes mean instructors have more time for students.\n\nIn third year you may choose a concentration: Accounting, Business Information and Analytics (BIMA), Financial Planning, Human Resources Management, International Business and Logistics, or Marketing. Students wanting to declare a concentration should fill out the BBA Concentration Declaration Form (pdf) and submit it to the Registrars Office.\n\n\n', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5257, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$40,693 ', 'USD', 'Business Administration Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two-year Business Administration diploma program have the skills and knowledge required to be effective managers in a demanding and changing workplace.\n\nThe first year of the diploma program provides a solid foundation in general business knowledge with courses in accounting/finance, communications, marketing, computing and organizational behaviour.\n\nThe second year offers the opportunity to concentrate (or focus) in a particular area of specialization.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5258, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$26,426 ', 'USD', 'North American Business Management Post Baccalaureate Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program builds knowledge about how to do business in North America for students from around the world.This full-time program is offered in an accelerated format and includes a work placement practicum. Concentrations are available in marketing, human resources, international strategy & entrepreneurship and finance & investment.\n\nInternational students and new permanent residents with an undergraduate degree completed outside of Canada can gain both North American business credentials and practical hands-on work experience in a North American organization.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5259, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$33,675 ', 'USD', 'North American Business Management Applied Post Baccalaureate Diploma (NABU Applied)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year diploma program builds knowledge about how to do business in North America for students from around the world.This full-time program is offered in an accelerated format and includes a work placement practicum. Concentrations are available in marketing, human resources, international strategy & entrepreneurship and finance & investment.\n\nInternational students and new permanent residents with an undergraduate degree completed outside of Canada can gain both North American business credentials and practical hands-on work experience in a North American organization.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5260, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$84,122 ', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Communication Studies Degree', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Bachelor of Communication Studies degree at CapU combines theory and practice in a project-based curriculum in various areas of strategic communication.In the program, students will learn critical approaches to media, communication and culture together with applied skills in writing, editing and public speaking.\n\nStudents can focus their expertise by taking classes across the spectrum of communication. Those who are interested in PR as career can opt for courses in public relations, media relations, crisis communication and organizational communication.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5261, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$40,693 ', 'USD', 'Communication Studies Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Communication Studies Diploma is a two-year, 60-credit program that gains the skills and abilities youll need start a career in communication, or to move on to upper level university courses in communication studies.\n\nIt provides a foundation for students who are aiming at careers in:\n\n.journalism\n\n.public, community and government affairs\n\n.media relations and media administration and research\n\n.communications project development\n\n.writing', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5262, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$41,759 ', 'USD', 'Tourism Management Co-op Education Diploma', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The program is simply the gateway to the tourism industry and a great choice to gain practical skills while enhancing your academic abilities.\n\nStudents will be ready to enter the workforce and make a positive impact directly after graduation with this co-op diploma. You\'ll learn about core tourism management functions, build connections with industry and job skills on your four-month accredited, supervised co-operative work term. They will study electives that meet your area of interest, ranging from hotel, adventure, events, eco-tourism and tourism planning.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5263, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$41,941 ', 'USD', 'Diploma in Tourism Management International', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This two year Tourism diploma makes you learn about the tourism industry and gain key management skills to use in your new career with the Diploma in Tourism Management International program at Capilano University.\n\nJoin your instructors on field trips, gain knowledge from guest speakers and take part in a 280-hour practicum placement as part of your concentrated tourism training.Participate in hands-on activities and make lifelong friends with classmates who are coming to study in North Vancouver from around the world.\n\nMajorly the diploma is for international students who speak English as a Second Language.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5264, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$85,815 ', 'USD', 'Bachelor of Early Childhood Care and Education Degree', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Bachelor of Early Childhood Care & Education (ECCE) offers students a range of academic and education courses that blend theory and practice in the early years, engaging with research and theory.\n\nThree core threads are intertwined throughout the degree: curriculum, childhoods, and leadership and advocacy. As part of your training, you\'ll be invited to engage in critically reflective practice, working to create classrooms of social justice and equity for children and families.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL);
