(5265, 82, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 135', NULL, '$76,262 ', 'USD', 'Bachelor Degree in Kinesiology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'In the program, you\'ll expand your expertise in the hands-on applications of kinesiology. Courses include physiology, biomechanics, active health, human behavior, anatomy, exercise psychology, leadership, and health policy. As you progress into the third- and fourth years of the program, you\'ll gain knowledge of research methods, data analysis, professional ethics, and field studies before moving into more focused training in your chosen specialty.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5266, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 7520', 'CAD ', 'Business Administration', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Eton college students who successfully complete the Business Administration Program diploma will receive up to 9 courses or 27 credit hours towards the Bachelor of Commerce degree at UCW which consists of 40 courses or 120 credits.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5267, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 11867', 'CAD ', 'Hospitality Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The 10 months diploma programe in Hospitality Management will prepare you to enter a wide range of employment opportunities within the thriving hospitality industry. It will develop your skills and knowledge in core areas such as front office and housekeeping operations, managing food and beverage, service leadership, convention management, guest services, and customer relations.\n\nThe program majorly focus on Hospitality management, Front office and housekeeping operations, Human resources management in hospitality and Convention management and services.\n\nAdditionally it provides knowledge of Food and beverage operations Food, beverage, and labour cost control, Canadian hospitality law and Supervision in hospitality industry.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5268, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 8450', 'CAD ', 'Business Administration Major in Hospitality Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The twenty months diploma programe focuses on the functional aspects of business and commerce, particularly on Canadas multibillion-dollar hospitality industry that is driven by the delivery of outstanding service. Through this program, you will learn everything about the business of hospitality, and gain a sharp understanding of key business practices in operations management, revenue management, and marketing techniques.\n\nGraduates of this program are eligible for admission to Royal Road Universitys Bachelor of Arts Major in International Hotel Management with full block transfer.\n\nProgram focus on Business Management, Global Business and Hospitality, Human Resources Management in Hospitality Convention Management and Services, and Social Responsibility, Ethics & Sustainability.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5269, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 8100', 'CAD ', 'Business Administration Major in Travel and Tourism Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This 18 months program develops students understanding of the various functional aspects of business and commerce, with focus on Canadas dynamic tourism industry. with the increasing demand of the travel and tourism sector s, the program responds to the need for global-minded professionals with business skills and insight. Graduates of this program are eligible for admission to Capilano Universitys Bachelor of Tourism Management.\n\nProgram focus on Business management global, Business and tourism, Human resources management in tourism, Destination marketing, Ethics and sustainable tourism, Accounting for business and tourism, Sales and relationship management and Service leadership.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5270, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 8426', 'CAD ', 'Hospitality and Tourism Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Eton College students who successfully complete the Hospitality and Tourism Management diploma will receive up to 51 credits towards Bachelor of Tourism Degree at Capilano University', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5271, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 8860', 'CAD ', 'Tourism & Hospitality Canadian Experience Co-op', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The two year Tourism & Hospitality Canadian Experience CoOp diploma program is designed to equip you with leadership skills to support the global hospitality and tourism economy, this program will prepare you to enter a wide range of employment opportunities within the two thriving industries.\n\nThe diploma program focus on Communications for the hotel and tourism industry, Human resources management, Canadian hospitality law, Front office and housekeeping operations, Food and beverage, operations Sales and relationship management, Transportation fares and costing tourism and Customer service', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5272, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 11867', 'CAD ', 'Travel, Tourism and Flight Attendant Preparation', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This 1 year Hospitality Management and Flight Attendant Preparation program is designed to develop the knowledge, skills, and attitude required to have an exciting career in the service-driven hospitality and aviation industry. You will also get to undergo a comprehensive flight attendant training in Vancouver.\n\nThe program was reviewed and approved by the registrar of the Private Training Institutions Branch (PTIB) of the BC Ministry of Advanced Education, Skills & Training.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5273, 88, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 150', NULL, 'CAD 8450', 'CAD ', 'Travel & Tourism Management', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The 8 months Travel and Tourism Management diploma program will make you to understand the tourism industry as a business while developing a service-driven attitude and exceptional communication skills. With the program you can discover a world of opportunities in the multibillion-dollar travel and tourism industry with this uniquely designed program that aims to help you develop the skills and knowledge required to work in businesses devoted to food and restaurant service, leisure, or cruise tourism.\n\nProgram focus on Tourism geography, Cross-cultural tourism, Sports and recreation management  laws and risks, Tourism products and service operations and Transportation fares and costing tourism.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5274, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Anthropolgy', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Anthropology is a fascinating and interdisciplinary field that will have you investigating the vast scope of human experience.\n\n\nYour studies will range in focus from the origin of our species and the development of the first known human civilizations to language and the diversity of cultures that exist today. Your studies will provide you with fundamentals, principles and theories as you explore the human experience from cultural, historical, geographical and sociological perspectives. Your curiosity may unearth new knowledge as you find yourself immersed in hands-on fieldwork and conducting applied research', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5275, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Classical Studies', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Classical Studies at Nipissing will take you deep into the ancient world.\n\nIn order to understand the present, it is vital to understand the past. If you join\n\nus in Classical Studies, you will join a long and cherished tradition of scholarship.\n\nClassical Studies, now more than ever, is a highly multidisciplinary program.\n\nYou will study ancient Greek and Roman history, myth and religion, literature,\n\ndrama, art and architecture, philosophy, law, social and political systems, class,\n\nslavery, military traditions, sport, cultural institutions, scientific and medical\n\nknowledge, and more.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5276, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Child and Family Studies', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Welcome to the Child and Family Studies (CHFS) program within the School of Human and Social Development at Nipissing University. The Child and Family Studies Program is unique with a particular focus on two thematic areas of study:\n\n    Human Development and Learning; and\n    Child and Family Well-Being: Issues, Services, and Social Justice. Students can pursue a Major, Specialization or Honors Specialization\n\nFurther, you want a career within child and adult developmental and/or behavior services, health/mental health services, child welfare, education, justice, government, or even the private sector, and have a real appetite for social justice and making a significant difference. You may choose to complete one of our 2 Applied Certificates in Applied Behavior Analysis or our Program Evaluation and Applied Research Certificate (PEAR) as you learn to improve systems and services for children, youth, or adults, across the social and human services sector.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5277, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-English Studies', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The primary way human beings communicate is through storytelling. Almost every interaction we have involves exchanging and analyzing stories, ideas, impressions and emotions. Given this fact of human culture, we see English Studies as teaching essential skills for life beyond the university.\n\n\nIn English, we challenge simplistic or superficial modes of thoughtor non-thoughtby finding out how texts of all sorts work. We learn from the past by reading classic works of literature, such as novels, plays and poetry. We also engage with contemporary culture by considering the texts that shape our current lives, such as movies, television, web-culture, graphic novels, theatre, and other media forms. With analytical reading, research and writing practice, we equip the citizens of the future with the skills of discernment, focus, resilience and adaptability that they will need to build their own careers and communities.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5278, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Environmental Geography', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Geography is the interdisciplinary study of our world, its physical characteristics like water, land forms, vegetation and climate as well as the relationships between people and the environment. You can choose between one of our three Geography degree options. The Bachelor of Arts in Geography provides a solid foundation in physical and human geography with a focus on the cultural, economic, political, and social influences. The Bachelor of Arts in Environmental Geography concentrates on the causes and effects of various environmental issues. The Bachelor of Science in Environmental and Physical Geography focuses on geography as an earth science and integrates mathematics, biology, geology, chemistry, and physics with geography-specific courses.??', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5279, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Gender Equality and Social Justice', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'GESJ is an interdisciplinary program with courses in the areas of Culture and Criticism, Power and Inequality, and Human Rights and Social Justice. We ask how race, class, colonialism, ability, sex, and gender intersect in everyday acts of power, oppression, activism, and resistance.\n\n\nThis program will provide you with highly transferrable skills in critical thinking, research, writing, argumentation, analysis, and communication.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5280, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Geography', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Geography is the interdisciplinary study of our world, its physical characteristics like water, landforms, vegetation and climate as well as the relationships between people and the environment. The Bachelor of Arts in Geography provides a solid foundation in physical and human geography with a focus on the cultural, economic, political, and social influences. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5281, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-History', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Department of History provides a personalized student experience within a collegial learning community dedicated to creativity, innovation, and excellence in teaching, research and scholarly activities.\n\n\nTo understand the past is to be able to place yourself in those contexts, to understand and think critically about the world, to empathize. Our program supports the formation of citizens as whole people. Indeed, this could be taken as the summation of our role. Learning in our department provides skills and a critically-informed perspective on society at large that is essential for an active and involved life in the twenty-first century.??', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5282, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Liberal Arts', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Students in Nipissings Liberal Arts program enjoy the flexibility of being able to design their own degree. Nipissings Liberal Arts program emphasizes breadth rather than specialization and allows individuals to develop a program that is suited to their personal interests and goals.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5283, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Criminal Justics - Corrections', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'At Nipissing you have the option to focus on one of our four streams: Policing, Corrections, Criminology or Criminal Justice Studies. Our flexible program is designed to give you a balanced combination of theory and practice. Through field placements, projects, and research, you will have opportunities to work alongside real criminal justice professionals.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5284, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Native Studies', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Indigenous Studies offers you an opportunity to learn about Indigenous cultures, philosophies, literature, histories, and contemporary issues that are central to this land that we live in. Its multidisciplinary approach reflects the different directions of the Medicine Wheel, so your studies will include the physical, intellectual, emotional, and spiritual aspects that are needed for true learning according to indigenous thought.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5285, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Philosophy', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Philosophy Program at Nipissing is small and student-focused: with an average of 35 full-time majors, students get to know and work closely with both their professors and their peers. The department is particularly committed to introducing students to the history of philosophy, from the ancient period to the present. The program is designed to work well either as a stand-alone degree or as a combined degree with other programs, and there are numerous philosophy courses offered each year that do not have prerequisites and that are popular electives for students in other programs.?', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5286, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Political Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'This degree program examines political topics that range from the foundations of international relations and foreign policy to Canadian politics.\n\n\nThe Political Science Program at Nipissing University offers courses of study in Political Theory, Canadian Politics, Comparative Politics, International Relations, and Public Administration.\n\n\n', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5287, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Psychology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Whether its working on brain tissue or learning about psychotherapy, Nipissings Psychology program has you covered. Award winning and funded Professors regularly encourage undergraduate students to join their lab groups. This provides students with invaluable research experience that helps them engage with their courses and prepare for future careers or graduate studies. Nipissing Universities relatively small size provides a huge advantage for students in terms of increased opportunities to get involved while not sacrificing on course offerings. The Psychology Department offers a full slate of courses that cover all major areas of the discipline.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5288, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Religions and Cultures', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Religions and Cultures program explores the religious cultures of our global society and the power of religious ideas in shaping us and our worlds.\n\nIn this program we investigate the major religious traditions of the world, as well as the role of religious ideas and values in culture, politics, art, media and popular culture. Our courses look at religion in relation to the Paranormal, Violence, Non-Violence, Cults, Gender, the Environment, Politics, Atheism, Death and Immortality, Animals and Evil to name just a few.\n\n\n', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5289, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Social Welfare and Social Development', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our interdisciplinary program is unique in Canada in both name and content. It focuses on inequality and the groups that have been underrepresented in the distribution of resources, opportunities, and power. Our students graduate with a thorough understanding of the causes and consequences of inequality in global, national, and local contexts, and an ability to formulate options for improving collective well-being.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5290, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Sociology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'If you choose to study Sociologythe study of human societiesyoull be entering into a fascinatingly broad discipline. Youll explore the sociological influences of many topics like the family, workplace, education, medicine, demographics, and the criminal justice system.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5291, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Economics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, '?Economics at Nipissing will introduce you to theories and economic models that will give you a solid framework for understanding how the world works. The structure of the Canadian economy, public policy, money, banking and financial institutions, the labour market, and the inter-dependence of nations in the global economy are all topics you will come to grasp with confidence.\n\n\nYou will be introduced to theories and policies related to Canadian and international economic development, and will examine social science issues like poverty, inequality, education, health, migration, agriculture and foreign aid.?', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5292, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Philosophy Program at Nipissing is small and student-focused: with an average of 35 full-time majors, students get to know and work closely with both their professors and their peers. The department is particularly committed to introducing students to the history of philosophy, from the ancient period to the present. The program is designed to work well either as a stand-alone degree or as a combined degree with other programs, and there are numerous philosophy courses offered each year that do not have prerequisites and that are popular electives for students in other programs.?', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5293, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Computer Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Computer Science program provides a strong foundation in computer science theory and in its practical applications including neural networks, artificial intelligence, robotics, graphics, computer security, software engineering, and game design. This will allow you to tailor your degree to be more applied or theoretical by selecting courses that align with your interests, and you will be supported by faculty who are genuinely interested in providing you with the skills to make your dreams a reality. You also have the option of simultaneously attaining a Certificate in Game Design and Development.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5294, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Criminal Justice', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'In the Criminal Justice Studies stream, you will take a wide variety of courses that will give you broad knowledge of the Criminal Justice system. You will also take courses in Sociology and Psychology, and you will learn how they relate to the field of Criminal Justice.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5295, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Criminology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Criminology Stream\n\nIn the Criminology stream, you will learn how to understand essential theories and methodologies used in the Criminology field. This stream gives you essential skills in communication, statistics, and analysis. We regularly offer courses in special topics like Women and the Criminal Justice System, and Youth in Conflict with the Law.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5296, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA)-Policing streams', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Policing Stream\n\nAs a student in the Policing stream, you will examine the criminal code, the young offenders system, and learn the skills and techniques you need for a successful career in policing. You will complete courses at both Nipissing University and Canadore College, and graduate with a college diploma and a university degree in just four years! Ethical reasoning and community policing are also key concepts in this stream.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5297, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Business\nAdministration (BBA)-Accounting', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'not available', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5298, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Business\nAdministration (BBA)-Business Administration', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'If you want to prepare for a career, and for life in general, Nipissings School of Business offers a unique approach to learning that gives you more than a degree. Along with core business knowledge, our faculty will help you develop professional and social skills. The programs combination of theoretical background, practical skills, experience, independent thinking, and problem solving will give you an advantage and better chance of success in a competitive market.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5299, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Business\nAdministration (BBA)-Human Resource ', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The School of Business offers a series certifcate to meet the needs of students wishing to learn about business in shorter periods of time compared to a typical degree program. ', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5300, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Fine Arts-NA', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'As a student registered with any of the three major areas of study in the Department of Fine and Performing Arts at Nipissing University (AHVS, Studio, and Film), you will have access to unique research and exhibition opportunities that foster professional development through exciting and interactive collaborative ventures with senior artists, gallery owners and community leaders.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5301, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Biology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Students at Nipissing explore Biology through enriched lab and field activitiesgaining practical experience through hands-on interaction. Those who are most interested in ecological or environmental forms of Biology can amass diverse field experiences through outdoor labs, field trips, Field Camps, and research studies performed in numerous nearby ecosystems. Students who are most interested in laboratory, greenhouse, or health-related Biology, can gain a wealth of skills and experience through exciting cutting-edge activities and research projects performed in our indoor research facilities, using top-of-the-line analytical equipment.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5302, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Computer Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Computer Science program provides a strong foundation in computer science theory and in its practical applications including neural networks, artificial intelligence, robotics, graphics, computer security, software engineering, and game design. This will allow you to tailor your degree to be more applied or theoretical by selecting courses that align with your interests, and you will be supported by faculty who are genuinely interested in providing you with the skills to make your dreams a reality. You also have the option of simultaneously attaining a Certificate in Game Design and Development.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5303, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Data Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Students learn the principles and methods of data science and their applications. Students engage with Big Data and apply methods to work with these data. Topics include: characteristics of big data; basics of cloud computing and distributed data processing; the need for data science and data analytics; applications; introduction to visual techniques.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5304, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Liberal Science  Sequence in two of\nBiology, Computer Science, Environmental Science, Geology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Liberal Science\n\nWelcome to the Liberal Science Program at Nipissing?\n\nNipissings Liberal Science program provides students with a broad-based understanding of a number of scientific disciplines. General in nature and flexible in structure, Nipissings Liberal Science program focuses on the basic concepts and orientations of modern science, and considers its role in todays society.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5305, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'At Nipissing, we combine a strong foundation of academic theory with an emphasis on research.\n\nMath opens up all kinds of career opportunities, from engineering to business to teaching, and more. You can even learn how to design computer games, if you opt for the Certificate in Game Design and Development.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5306, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Environmental Biology and\nTechnology', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our Environmental Biology and Technology (ENBT) program specializes in providing you with the knowledge and skills required to study Environmental Biology from many perspectives. You will receive the double-benefit of combining the academic education provided by Nipissing University with the practical and technical skills taught by our colleagues at Canadore College. All courses are completed within four years, and you will emerge withbotha university degreeanda college diploma. As well, there are a number ofspecial certificates that ENBT students can earn.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5307, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science (BSc)-Environment and Physical\nGeography', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Geography is the interdisciplinary study of our world, its physical characteristics like water, landforms, vegetation and climate as well as the relationships between people and the environment.The Bachelor of Science in Environmental and Physical Geography focuses on geography as an earth science and integrates mathematics, biology, geology, chemistry, and physics with geography-specific courses.??', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5308, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Science in Nursing-NA', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Our Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BScN) program is offered through an educational partnership with Canadore College. Classes are learner-centred, and are taught by skilled faculty from both schools.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5309, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Social Work (BSW)-NA', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'While the roots of Nipissing University extend back to the 1900s with the North Bay Normal School, Nipissing University College was formed in 1967 as an affiliate of Laurentian University. Nipissing University received its charter as an independent University in 1992. \n\nToday, Nipissing is proud to be a primarily undergraduate university with a reputation for excellence in teacher education, arts, science and professional programs. Students will find themselves in a high-quality academic environment that is student-focused and based on personal teaching practices, innovative approaches to learning, and a growing research culture.\n\nNipissing is committed to playing a positive role in the educational, social, cultural, and economic life in all of the communities it serves.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5310, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Bachelor of Arts (BA) or Bachelor of Science (BSc) combined with Bachelor of Commerce-NA', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The student will be studying Arts subjects along with the Commerce subjects', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5311, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Concurrent Bachelor of Fine\nArts (BFA)/Bachelor of\nEducation (BEd)\nPrimary/Junior\nJunior/Intermediate\nIntermediate/Senio', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Students graduate with a Dual Degree  an honours undergraduate degree in their discipline of choice and a Bachelor of Education degree.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5312, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Concurrent Bachelor of\nScience (BSc)/Bachelor of\nEducation (BEd)\nPrimary/Junior\nJunior/Intermediate\nIntermediate/Senior-', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Concurrent Education route includes a set of courses and a non-credit practical experience, that when taken as part of an Honours undergraduate degree, provide preparation for the Bachelor of Education program. Concurrent education allows Nipissing University students the opportunity to assess their suitability for and interest in a BEd before their undergraduate degrees are complete.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5313, 96, NULL, NULL, 'CAD 110', NULL, '21,000 CAD', 'CAD ', 'Concurrent Bachelor of\nScience (BSc)/Bachelor of\nEducation (BEd)\nPrimary/Junior\nJunior/Intermediate\nIntermediate/Senior-', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Concurrent Education route includes a set of courses and a non-credit practical experience, that when taken as part of an Honours undergraduate degree, provide preparation for the Bachelor of Education program. Concurrent education allows Nipissing University students the opportunity to assess their suitability for and interest in a BEd before their undergraduate degrees are complete.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
