(5404, 84, NULL, NULL, 'USD 40', NULL, '29,400', 'USD', 'UG-Mathematics: Elementary Education', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Castleton\'s Math degree brings accuracy and rigor to the quest for discovering patterns, both abstract and concrete.\n\n\nAs a math major, you will acquire a broad and solid base in mathematics which will enable both further study and application.\n\n\nOur knowledgeable mathematics faculty teach in the realms of pure mathematics, applied mathematics, and statistics to inspire you to appreciate and understand these disciplines.\n\n\nHighlights of the Mathematics Program\n\nAs a student, you will be encouraged to provide insight into new and existing courses, attend seminars, and to participate in mathematical activities at the local, regional, and national levels.\n\nA Mathematics degree from Castleton opens a wide array of opportunities, including entering a professional environment or entering a graduate program at the master\'s or doctoral level.\n\nThe University\'s small class sizes will provide you with an individualized learning experience and coursework will allow you to conduct research projects under the guidance of our experienced faculty.\n\nDegree tracks in Mathematics, Mathematics Secondary Education, Mathematics Elementary Education, and Statistics.\n\nPrepare for a big test or get help understanding complex math concepts with the Math Clinic.\n\nThis major is for students interested in teaching mathematics at the elementary school level. Mathematics teachers play a critical role in our society, and students who complete this program are in great demand.\n\n\nStudents who complete the mathematics major are able to:\n\n\nAnalyze and solve real-world problems using a variety of mathematical techniques,\n\nConvey mathematical information in effective ways,\n\nChoose and employ appropriate technology,\n\nSecure desired employment or gain admission to graduate or professional programs of study.\n\nIn addition, students who complete a program leading to teaching:\n\n\nAcquire a strong foundation in both mathematics content and teaching methods,\n\nGain experience working with students through tutorships and internships.\n\nTo be accepted into the BA.MAT.EED program, students must obtain a positive letter of recommendation from a faculty member; receive approval from the Mathematics Department chair; select an academic advisor in the Mathematics Department.\n\nCareers With a Math Degree\n\nA diligent and highly motivated student with a background in mathematics will find many career opportunities. Castleton graduates work successfully as:\n\n\nStatisticians\n\nMarket researchers\n\nComputer programmers\n\nSystems analysts\n\nBusiness administrators\n\nManagers\n\nMany Castleton graduates teach mathematics in high school, middle school, or elementary school. At all levels of teaching, there is a critical need for quality mathematics instruction.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL);
