lete a program leading to teaching:\n\n\nAcquire a strong foundation in both mathematics content and teaching methods,\n\nGain experience working with students through tutorships and internships.\n\nTo be accepted into the BA.MAT.SED program, students must obtain a positive letter of recommendation from a faculty member; receive approval from the Mathematics Department chair; and select an academic advisor in the Mathematics Department.\n\nCareers With a Math Degree\n\nA diligent and highly motivated student with a background in mathematics will find many career opportunities. Castleton graduates work successfully as:\n\n\nStatisticians\n\nMarket researchers\n\nComputer programmers\n\nSystems analysts\n\nBusiness administrators\n\nManagers\n\nMany Castleton graduates teach mathematics in high school, middle school, or elementary school. At all levels of teaching, there is a critical need for quality mathematics instruction.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5406, 84, NULL, NULL, 'USD 40', NULL, '29,400', 'USD', 'UG-Mathematics: Statistics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Castleton Universitys Physical Education program has a long history of preparing educators to deliver quality physical education in our schools. It is also known for teaching professionals to provide health, recreation, and fitness opportunities within our communities.\n\n\nStudents who wish to teach in schools apply for admittance into our rigorous teacher preparation program, which prepares candidates for teacher licensure. The program culminates with a semester-long student teaching experience.\n\n\nArea employers are aware of the Universitys enduring reputation and commitment to producing exceptional health and physical education teachers.\n\n\nALUMNI SPOTLIGHT: Phil Hall used his Physical Education degree to enter school administration\n\n\nHighlights of the Program\n\nPhysical Education majors gain quality off-campus experience throughout the program. Starting in your first year, you can begin working with students in local schools across a variety of age groups\n\nAs a student, you can take advantage of professional development opportunities by attending state, regional, and national conferences, and by participating in a workshop series organized by faculty\n\nPhysical Education Concentrations\n\nElementary and Secondary Education\n\nYou will earn Physical Education Teacher Licensure for grades pre- K-12. Standards for the program are aligned with the teacher education guidelines of the Society of Health and Physical Educators of America and the Vermont Agency of Education.\n\n\nHealth and Physical Activity Promotion\n\nHealth and Physical Activity Promotion will prepare for careers in non- school settings such as public health departments, government agencies, hospitals, and medical centers, youth programs and camps, fitness centers, recreation departments, and non- profit community organizations.\n\n\nYou can choose minors in Adventure Recreation, Coaching, Fitness Science or Health\n\n\nCareer Opportunities With a Physical Education Degree\n\nGraduates of our program work all over New England, New York, and beyond. A Physical Education Degree can set you on a path for a career as:\n\n\nAdaptive physical education specialist\n\nAdventure education leader\n\nAllied health services\n\nAthletic coach\n\nAthletic director\n\nAthletic trainer\n\nBusiness relations director\n\nCollege professor\n\nCompliance coordinator\n\nCurriculum coordinator\n\nDance instructor\n\nEarly childhood motor skills instructor\n\nElementary school teacher\n\nExercise physiologist\n\nExercise psychologist\n\nFacilities and operations director\n\nFan relations\n\nFitness instructor\n\nGeriatric fitness and rehabilitation specialist\n\nHealth education teacher\n\nHealth promotion specialist\n\nHigh school sports coach\n\nHigh school teacher\n\nMiddle school teacher\n\nMovement education specialist\n\nNutritionist\n\nOccupational therapist\n\nOutdoor recreation specialist\n\nPara-educator\n\nPhysical activities specialist\n\nPhysical education specialist\n\nPhysical education teacher\n\nPhysical therapist\n\nPhysicians assistant\n\nPost-secondary school teacher\n\nPre-school teacher\n\nProfessional athlete\n\nPublic health professional\n\nRecreation manager\n\nReferee\n\nSales representative\n\nSchool principal\n\nSki instructor\n\nSports announcer\n\nSports information director\n\nSports team manager\n\nStrength & conditioning coach\n\nSummer camp director\n\nTeacher assistant\n\nYouth sports camp director\n\nYouth sports coach\n\nTicket operations manager\n\nUmpire\n\nWater sports director\n\nPhysical Education Outside the Classroom\n\nYou will gain early, frequent, and continuous teaching experiences in both school and community settings including:\n\n\nObservation in local schools\n\nSemester-long student teaching\n\nWorking directly with special populations of students\n\nOpportunities in coaching youth sports and activity programs\n\nPhysical Education majors sponsor community events with groups such as Vermont Special Olympics, Castleton Lions Club, and the Society for Health and Physical Education (SHAPE-VT). Our students also take opportunities to network with our physical education alumni at state and regional conferences.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5407, 84, NULL, NULL, 'USD 40', NULL, '29,400', 'USD', 'UG-Media & Communication: Digital Media', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'As a Media and Communication student, students will thrive in a project-based environment that balances theory and practice.Working closely with faculty and peers, students will study the ways media interacts with society and produce video, news, social media, websites, and scripts. There are many opportunities to sharpen your skills and demonstrate your work.\n\nStudents can work toward a bachelors degree in Media and Communication with concentrations in Media and Communication, Media Studies, Video & Film Production, Journalism, Public Relations, or Digital Media. Additionally, the program offers an associate degree and minors in communication and cinema studies.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5408, 84, NULL, NULL, 'USD 40', NULL, '29,400', 'USD', 'UG-Media & Communication: Journalism', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'As a Media and Communication student, you will thrive in a project-based environment that balances theory and practice.\n\n\nWorking closely with faculty and peers, you will study the ways media interacts with society and produce video, news, social media, websites, and scripts. There are many opportunities to sharpen your skills and demonstrate your work. Those include The Spartan newspaper and website, Castleton Internet Radio, the Content Lab, independent projects, and internships. Castletons Media and Communication alumni have gone on to create major network programming, garner credits in Academy Award-winning movies, and write and edit for large daily newspapers. They have also designed major websites, excelled at graduate school, provided public information for large businesses and non-profits, teach in high schools and universities, practice law, and a wide array of other professional activities. Bachelor of Arts graduates in Media & Communication will be able to:\n\n\nUnderstand media from social, economic, political, ethical, and global perspectives.\n\nEffectively research and analyze media material.\n\nProduce high quality media in visual, oral, and written forms.\n\nEffectively apply media and communication skills in a rapidly changing real world environment.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
