(5435, 84, NULL, NULL, 'USD 40', NULL, '29,400', 'USD', 'UG-Health Science', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'The Castleton University Natural Sciences Department offers a bachelor\'s degree in Health Science that prepares you for admission to graduate programs in physical therapy, occupational therapy, and professional work in health care fields.\n\n\nHealth Science majors take a core of essential courses, such as Human Anatomy and Physiology, Chemistry, and Physics. A solid foundation in these disciplines is important to anyone with an interest in human health.\n\n\nCastletons Health Science major also includes a great deal of flexibility, allowing students to choose courses that will prepare them for the specific graduate program or career they seek.\n\n\nHighlights of the Health Science Program\n\nCastleton has strong undergraduate programs in Exercise Science and Kinesiology, and many classes in these areas may be used to satisfy Health Science requirements. This allows you to take some specialized courses that can set you apart from other applicants for graduate school.\n\nAll Health Science majors complete an internship. For most students, this will be a job shadowing experience with one of our local healthcare professionals during the academic year or, if more convenient, with a healthcare provider near your home over the summer.\n\nCastleton has an articulation agreement with Russell Sage College Graduate School in the Albany, N.Y., area that offers preferred admission of our graduates to Sages Occupational and Physical Therapy programs, as long as our students meet certain criteria. After graduation from Castleton, students can go on to earn a Masters in Occupational Therapy (MS-OT) or a Doctorate in Physical Therapy (DPT) from Sage.\n\nHealth Science Outside of the Classroom\n\nAll students complete an internship or job shadowing experience. Castleton will help arrange your field experience with one of many local health care providers, or if more convenient, with a provider near your home over the summer. Field experience is a valuable step in choosing a career path, and practical experience is typically required by graduate programs in the health sciences.\n\n\nOpportunities in Health Science\n\nCastleton will give you a variety of options during your educational and professional career path. One-on-one advising sessions with faculty help match each students undergraduate coursework with prerequisites for employment or graduate/professional programs.\n\n\nYou will also have the opportunity to choose courses from an array of disciplines including Athletic Training, Biology, Exercise Science, and more.\n\n\nThe program provides students the ability to compliment a Health Science major with a minor in Health Promotion in preparation for becoming Certified Health Education Specialists. Additionally, Castleton offers cooperative agreements in:\n\n\nMasters in Occupational Therapy\n\nDoctor of Physical Therapy\n\nDoctor of Pharmacy\n\nHealth Science Outcomes\n\nOur Health Science graduates are broadly trained and have excellent laboratory skills. Many graduates are working in hospitals or laboratories, in medical equipment sales, and other health-related careers. Graduates have an excellent record of success in gaining admission to a variety of graduate programs for:\n\n\nDoctor of Physical Therapy\n\nOccupational Therapy\n\nPhysician Assistant\n\nNurse Practitioner\n\nOsteopathic Medicine\n\nPublic Health Professional', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
(5436, 84, NULL, NULL, 'USD 40', NULL, '29,400', 'USD', 'UG-Health Science: Pre-Athletic Training (MSAT)', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '', 1, 'Castletons Health Science program prepares students for admission to graduate programs in athletic training, physical therapy, occupational therapy, and professional work in a competitive job market. Our Health Science program offers three distinct concentration tracks, allowing you to focus your studies in a specific area that interests you.\n\n\nWhy Pursue a Health Science Degree at Castleton?\n\nGain essential healthcare knowledge and skills. A bachelors degree in Health Science provides you with professional knowledge and skills that will be essential for future employment. All Health Science majors complete an internship or clinical experience, allowing you to gain hands-on experience before you graduate.\n\nImprove the lives of others. Castletons Health Science courses are focused on health care, intervention, and prevention, which means youll be equipped with tools to improve the quality of life of those in your community.\n\nBe ready for grad school. Our three concentrations in General Health Science, Pre-Professional, and Pre-Athletic Training prepare you for entrance into graduate school, including Castletons Master of Athletic Training. Castleton graduates also receive preferred admission to Russell Sage College Graduate School Occupational and Physical Therapy programs. Students can go on to earn a Masters in Occupational Therapy (MS-OT) or a Doctorate in Physical Therapy (DPT) from Russell Sage. Students can also participate in the 3+4 Pharmacy Degree with Albany College of Pharmacy & Health Sciences.\n\nExplore the Three Concentrations\n\nPre-Athletic Training\n\nOur Pre-Athletic Training degree track prepares you to continue your education in Castletons CAATE accredited Master of Athletic training program. This accelerated program allows you to complete your bachelors and masters degrees in as little as five years. Students may choose to complete the four-year Health Science degree before applying to the MAT program.\n\n\nLearn more about our Pre-Athletic Training concentration ?\n\n\nPre-Professional\n\nOur Pre-Professional degree track prepares you to apply to professional programs in the health care field, such as chiropractic medicine, occupational therapy, and physical therapy.\n\n\nGeneral Health Science\n\nOur General Health Science degree track prepares you for a wide range of career paths in health-related fields or graduate programs.\n\n\nWhat Careers in Health Science Can I Pursue?\n\nGraduates of Castletons Health Science program have gone on to successful careers in a variety of settings, including hospitals, laboratories, fitness centers and sports clubs, sports medicine clinics, private agencies, and more.\n\n\nYoull graduate prepared for careers including:\n\n\nPersonal Trainer\n\nPatient Care Advocate\n\nParamedic\n\nMedical Assistant\n\nMedical Equipment Sales Representative\n\nHealth Education Specialist\n\nView Castletons Career Outcomes ?\n\n\nWhat Youll Learn\n\nAs a student in Castletons Health Science program, you will take courses that will strengthen your knowledge of the human body and how it works. The Health Science core courses help to establish a broad knowledge and skill set, with opportunities to explore certain topics in greater depth as part of your concentration or through a variety of elective courses.\n\n\nSample Courses\n\nHuman Anatomy & Physiology I\n\nFoundations of Health and Exercise Professions\n\nHuman Growth and Development\n\nCommunity Health\n\nClinical Exercise Testing and Prescription\n\nStrength Training Principles\n\nView Health Science courses ?\n\n\nMeet our Health Science Faculty\n\nYour professors bring a wealth of knowledge and experience from working as professionals and as skilled researchers in their respective fields. Castletons faculty are here to help you make connections for internships and future careers.', NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL),
