p;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ownership of Your Data</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nothing herein transfers any ownership of Your Data to University Bureauin its original form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Data and Feedback of High Quality</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Without limiting the foregoing, University Bureau does not evaluate the quality of Your Data in any way. The correctness of Your Data given by you to the University Bureau may be relied on by University Bureau, University Bureau Partners, and any third parties to whom University Bureau is entitled to disclose Your Data under this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any feedback you receive on Your Data is exclusively based on the compliance requirements of University Bureau Partners and is not the result of any specific examination of the data by the University Bureau or any judgment exercised by University Bureau regarding Your Data. Consent to Processing of Your Data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The collection, processing, transmission, and disclosure of Your Data by the University Bureau, University Bureau Partners, and their service providers is an essential part of the University Bureau. You hereby expressly consent to the University Bureau&#39;s provision of Your Data to any University Bureau Partner, visa agencies, English test score organizations, professional bodies, service providers to the University Bureau (including our hosting providers).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau communications (including marketing and informational e-mails) regarding the University Bureau and University Bureau&#39;s products and services; and</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau&#39;s collection, usage, and other processing activities as outlined in University Bureau&#39;s Privacy Policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your personal information will be processed in accordance with the Privacy and Cookies Policy of the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regardless of the foregoing, the University Bureau reserves the right to disclose any personal information necessary to comply with any applicable law, legal process, or governmental or regulatory authority requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Data Retention in Other Jurisdictions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You acknowledge that owing to the nature of the University Bureau, Your Data may be stored on servers located outside of Canada, over which the University Bureau has no direct control. Using the University Bureau, Your Data may become subject to the Applicable Laws of the jurisdiction in which such servers are located or the conditions of agreements governing the hosting of data on such servers for the duration that Your Data is hosted on such servers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>De-Identified Data</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau may use the data you provide or will provide to third parties, Your Data, and any data related to the University Bureau, in aggregated form or in a manner that does not identify you, subject to University Bureau&#39;s Privacy Policy and UB may use that data for analytics and marketing to third parties. Any intellectual property rights in the output of the University Bureau&#39;s usage of any such De-identified Data will be owned by University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Your Access Information</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To allow you to use the University Bureau website, University Bureau will give you with necessary information (IDs, passwords). The Access Information is provided on the premise that it is personal to you and that no one other than you or your authorized representatives will be able to use it to access the University Bureau Website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Your Representations and Warranties</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you have reached the age of majority in your jurisdiction of residence and have the legal authority to enter into a binding legal obligation;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will not allow anyone other than yourself or your authorized designate to gain access to the University Bureau through your University Bureau account or otherwise using your Access Information;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will only use the University Bureau in accordance with this Agreement and Applicable Law;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will comply with all applicable intellectual property laws in your use of the University Bureau and will not infringe, violate, or misappropriate the intellectual property rights of any third party;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will comply with any University Bureau Partner policies and procedures applicable to your Application;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Data is true, accurate, current, and complete, and you will promptly notify University Bureau or update Your Data on the University bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you hired a Recruiter to give Your Data on your behalf to use the University Bureau, you must: (A) the Recruiter has a genuine educational interest in access to your educational records and information (the &quot;Educational Records&quot;); and (B) the Recruiter has access to such Educational Records in the United States.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At any stage of a visa application or proceeding, you will not seek immigration or visa-related advice from a Recruiter unless you have confirmed that the Recruiter complies with Applicable Law in the country to which you are applying and, if required, that the Recruiter has registration under such Applicable Law;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will be solely responsible for all activities involving the University Bureau undertaken by you or your designates;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will not use the University Bureau to provide commercial services to, or for the benefit of, any third party;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will not pay a related fee or other consideration to any unauthorized Recruiters for any immigration or visa-related advice unless they have confirmed to you that they are qualified under Applicable Law;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you have the legal right and authorization to enter into this Agreement, grant the rights and licenses set forth in this Agreement, use University Bureau, and post or upload any content to University Bureau&#39;s website or otherwise supply such content and Your Data to University Bureau;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You have all legal rights to use the University Bureau, including the right to access the Content, make the Application, and give Your Data in your home country and the jurisdiction where the University Bureau you are applying to is located.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you agree to obtain all necessary authorizations from all third parties for your use of any third-party data in conjunction with the University Bureau;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you are not located in a country that is subject to a Canadian or US Government embargo or sanctions that would prevent you from becoming a student;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you are not listed on any Canadian or US Governmental or Regulatory Authority lists of prohibited or restricted parties;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will guarantee that your use of the University Bureau does not disrupt, impair, or harm any software, system, network, or data utilized by anyone, including the University Bureau and other University Bureau users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will not use the University Bureau in any way to commit or attempt to commit a crime or to facilitate the commission of any crime or other illegal or tortious acts, such as infringement of intellectual property rights, fraudulent activities, deceptive impersonation, or activities that violate any third party&#39;s privacy rights;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will not tamper with or compromise the University Bureau&#39;s security measures in any way;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will not alter, edit, remove, or otherwise tamper with or compromise any Content or features accessible through the University Bureau website, including the forms, Content delivery, and display functions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will help the University Bureau and any Governmental or Regulatory Authorities in investigating or determining whether there has been a breach of this Agreement or Applicable Law by cooperating with the University Bureau and providing the information requested by the University Bureau; and</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will abide by the terms and conditions of any agreements you enter into with third parties, including the University Bureau Partners, the service providers for any Internet services you use in conjunction with the University Bureau, and the hardware providers for any mobile device or other computing equipment you use to access the University Bureau, to the extent that such agreements impose additional restrictions on your use of the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Use of the University Bureau: Restrictions and Limitations</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Program Access&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You acknowledge that University Bureau has agreements with you to allow you to make an Application to University Bureau through the University Bureau. Not all educational study programs of such University Bureau Partners may be offered as Programs available to you through the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Policies of Usage</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University Bureau will be bound by the University Bureau&#39;s usage regulations, which will be supplied to you from time to time, including in electronic form by posting on the University Bureau&#39;s website. Limitations on data storage space and equipment and/or software requirements are examples of such rules. You are solely responsible for ensuring that such policies are followed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Equipment</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Except for University Bureau&#39;s computer systems and networks, you are solely responsible for the selection, implementation, installation, maintenance, and performance of any and all equipment, software, and services used in conjunction with using the University Bureau, including your choice and use of your Internet Service Provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Data Integrity and Back-up</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You realize and accept that the University Bureau cannot guarantee data integrity and that backing up any of the data you use in association with the University Bureau is exclusively your responsibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University Bureau is not developed or licensed for inherently dangerous, time-sensitive, or mission-critical use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau will not:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Copy, reproduce, modify, enhance, improve, alter, reverse engineer, disassemble, deconstruct, translate, decrypt, reverse compile, or convert the University Bureau, in whole or in part, into human-readable form;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>distribute, assign, license, sublicense, lease, rent, transfer, sell, or otherwise provide access to the University Bureau, in whole or in part, to any third party on a temporary or permanent basis;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>removing, defacing, covering, or otherwise obscuring any proprietary rights notice or identification on the Content (including, without limitation, any copyright notice);&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>using the in any way that violates the University Bureau&#39;s use parameters;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>attempting to hack the University Bureau or any communication initiated by or made through the University Bureau, or to defeat or overcome any encryption or other technical protection methods implemented concerning the University Bureau, data, Content, or programming transmitted, processed, or stored by University Bureau or other University Bureau users;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>collect any information or communication about University Bureau users by monitoring, interdicting, or intercepting any process or communication initiated by the University Bureau website or by developing or using any software or other process or method that engages or assists in engaging in any of the aforementioned;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use any type of bot, spider, virus, clock, timer, counter, worm, software lock, drop dead device, packet-sniffer, Trojan-horse routing, trap door, time bomb, or any other codes or instructions that are designed to monitor, distort, delete, damage, or disassemble the University Bureau or its ability to communicate and perform the Servicing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Authorize, permit, or otherwise acquiesce in any third party engaging in, or attempting to engage in, any of the actions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Modifications to the Terms and Conditions; Modifications to the University Bureau; Right to Edit and Remove Your Information; Suspension or Termination of Employment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau maintains the right to modify these Terms and Conditions at any time and without prior notice. Following any modifications to these Terms and Conditions, your continuing access to or use the University Bureau represents your acceptance of those changes. You are responsible for reviewing these Terms and Conditions regularly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau reserves the right to update, suspend, or discontinue the University Bureau at any time and without notice, including the availability of any content and from time to time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau reserves the right to review Your Data stored in files or programs on University Bureau&#39;s servers to verify your compliance with this Agreement, notwithstanding anything to the contrary herein. University Bureau reserves the right to delete or remove any of Your Data that it deems unlawful, obscene, abusive, or otherwise objectionable in its sole discretion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau may, without responsibility, set limits on the University Bureau and terminate or restrict your access to parts or all of it. University Bureau will give you advance notice of such modifications, limitations, or discontinuances; nevertheless, you agree that such notification may not be possible in all cases and that the University Bureau will have no liability for its failure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose your use of the University Bureau constitutes, in University Bureau&#39;s sole discretion, a threat to University Bureau or any third party&#39;s computer systems, networks, files, materials, or other data, or a breach of this Agreement. In that case, the University Bureau reserves the right to revoke your access to the University Bureau for any abusive conduct or fraudulent use and cease the University Bureau temporarily or permanently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If: (a) you breach this Agreement or the documents it incorporates by reference; (b) University Bureau is unable to verify or authenticate any information you provide; or (c) University Bureau believes that your actions may cause financial loss or legal liability, University Bureau may limit your activity, issue a warning, temporarily suspend, indefinitely suspend, or terminate your account and refuse to provide University Bureau to you, University Bureau may limit your activity, issue a warning, temporarily suspend, indefinitely suspend, or terminate your account</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Partners, other users, or the University Bureau. University Bureau may take any additional legal, equitable, or technological action that it deems appropriate under the circumstances and the acts listed above. If this Agreement is terminated, the University Bureau will not be liable to you or any third person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University Bureau maintains the right to investigate any alleged violations of this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For University Bureau to enforce the terms and conditions of this Agreement, you will cooperate with: (A) Governmental or Regulatory Authorities in the investigation of suspected criminal violations; (B) the University Bureau investigating academic fraud or other misdemeanors relating to your Application or otherwise; and (C) system administrators at Internet service providers, networks or computing facilities, and other content providers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Your Responsibility to Report Errors</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree to promptly and accurately report to University Bureau any actual or apparent errors, problems, non-conformities, or other difficulties and any other information reasonably requested by University Bureau to assist in resolving such errors, issues, non-conformities or other challenges. You hereby consent to the University Bureau collecting, processing, transmitting, and disclosing such information for the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Submissions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any suggestions, bug reports, or other communications about the functionality of the University Bureau or University Bureau&#39;s website that you send to the University Bureau by any means (each, a &quot;Submission&quot;) are considered non-confidential. They may be disseminated or used by University Bureau or any third party without compensation or liability to you, whether for inclusion in the University Bureau or otherwise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You grant University Bureau, its affiliates, and successors a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, sublicensable, and transferable license to use, copy, distribute, transmit, modify, develop, and prepare derivative works of any Submission on, through, or in connection with the Service, including to promote, improve, and creating the University Bureau. This provision does not apply to Personal Information covered by the Privacy Policy of the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fees, Payment, and Taxes</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fees</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree to pay all applicable fees in connection with the University Bureau, as specified in the University Bureau&#39;s regular price list, on the University Bureau&#39;s website, or as otherwise given to you. Fees for Canadian-related Applications are quoted and paid in Canadian dollars, whereas fees for USD-related Applications are quoted and payable in US dollars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Depending on the country from which you are applying, other characteristics applicable to applicants, and the related likelihood of an Application being successful due to Governmental or Regulatory Authority visa approvals, University Bureau may require you to pay an Application processing deposit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information on the Application processing deposit and the countries it will apply to may be found on the University Bureau website. The University Bureau has the right to amend it at any moment. The University Bureau website outlines the circumstances in which an Application processing deposit is refundable and those in which an Application processing deposit will not be refunded to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THE FOLLOWING SITUATIONS WILL NOT RETURN YOUR APPLICATION PROCESSING DEPOSIT: (A) YOU FAIL TO PROVIDE THE REQUIRED DOCUMENTS TO PROCESS THE APPLICATION; (B) YOUR VISA APPLICATION IS REJECTED, OR (C) YOU CANCEL YOUR APPLICATION BEFORE RECEIVING AN ADMISSION DECISION.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certain fees charged by University Bureau under this Agreement are set by University Bureau Partners or other third parties, and University Bureau has no control over the fee amount; instead, University Bureau remits such fees directly to the applicable University Bureau, a partner, or third party, and payment obligations are non-cancellable and fees paid are non-refundable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau reserves the right to amend such prices with appropriate notice, which can be accomplished by updating University Bureau&#39;s standard pricing list, which is available on the website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By continuing to use the University Bureau after such modifications, you agree to any additional or higher costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose you pay fees with a credit card. In that case, you allow University Bureau or its third-party payment processor to charge your credit card automatically for any costs owed to University Bureau. You will be liable for all fees and penalties incurred because your credit card is declined for any reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The foregoing will not limit the University Bureau&#39;s ability to exercise any legal or equitable rights it may have in relation to collecting any amounts due under this Agreement. You will be responsible for paying all reasonable fees and costs incurred by the University Bureau, including legal fees, to collect any overdue amounts or enforce any provision of this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Without limiting the above, University Bureau maintains the right to refuse to process any Application or portion thereof until all fees have been paid in full.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau will be entitled to charge interest on all outstanding amounts at the lesser of 1.5 percent per month or the maximum rate permitted by Applicable Law, such interest beginning on the due date for such payment, and any other rights and remedies available to the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Except for taxes based on University Bureau&#39;s net revenue, you are liable for and shall pay any taxes related to this Agreement. Unless otherwise specified, all amounts payable by you under this Agreement are exclusive of any tax, duty, levy, or similar government charge imposed by any jurisdiction, whether based on gross revenue, delivery, possession, or use of the University Bureau, the execution of this Agreement, or otherwise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are compelled to withhold taxes from payments due under this Agreement, the amount owing will be automatically raised to balance the tax, such that the amount paid to University Bureau equals the amount owed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You shall promptly provide to the applicable taxing authority copies of any official receipts showing payment of taxes owed under or in relation to this Agreement to the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Confidential Information</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Except to the extent necessary to conduct the Recruitment Services, you shall keep the terms of this Agreement and any information given by the University Bureau secret.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; You acknowledge that you may be exposed to Confidential Information during the term of this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Throughout the Term and beyond the termination of this Agreement, whether voluntarily or involuntary:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will keep all Confidential Information in strict confidence, take all necessary precautions to prevent unauthorized disclosure, and will not, directly or indirectly, disclose, allow access to, transmit, or transfer any Confidential Information to a third party without University Bureau&#39;s knowledge and express written consent;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you will not use, disclose, or reproduce the Confidential Information except as necessary to receive the Services and with University Bureau&#39;s knowledge and express written consent; and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will immediately notify University Bureau in writing of any misappropriation, disclosure, conversion, or misuse of any confidential information you become aware of.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While Your Data is in University Bureau&#39;s control, University Bureau will use reasonable commercial efforts to safeguard and keep it confidential, including implementing organizational and technical measures to protect your Personal Information, subject to University Bureau&#39;s ability to disclose Your Data as permitted under this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau may additionally keep and disclose Your Data to the following parties: I Governmental or Regulatory Authorities as required by Applicable Law: (ii) its professional advisers to the extent necessary to (A) allow University Bureau to comply with Applicable Law; or (B) defend or bring a claim arising from a breach of this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nondisclosure obligations under this Agreement will not apply to information that a Party can demonstrate:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>is, or becomes, readily available to the public other than as a result of a breach of this Agreement;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>was lawfully disclosed to a Party by a third party without any confidentiality obligation attached to such information;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>was lawfully known to a Party without any confidentiality obligation before the signing of this Agreement;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Was lawfully known to a Party without any confidentiality obligation before signing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Was independently produced or discovered by a Party outside of the execution of such Party&#39;s responsibilities under this Agreement, without reference to any Confidential Information acquired directly or indirectly from the disclosing Party.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon the University Bureau&#39;s request or the termination of this Agreement, you shall immediately return any Confidential Information in your custody or control to University Bureau (whether voluntary or involuntary).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because damages may not be an adequate remedy for any breach of your obligations under this agreement, you agree that University Bureau and any other remedies available will be entitled to obtain relief in the form of a temporary or permanent injunction to enforce your obligations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intellectual Property</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All right, titles, and interests in the University Bureau are retained by University Bureau or its third-party licensors. Copyright laws in Canada, the United States, and worldwide protect the University Bureau. In addition, the University Bureau may be protected by other intellectual property laws (including patent laws) and treaties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Under this Agreement, you do not acquire any intellectual property or other proprietary rights, including any right, title, or interest in and to patents, copyrights, trade-marks, industrial designs, confidential information, or trade secrets relating to the University Bureau, or any part thereof, whether registered or unregistered. University Bureau or its third-party licensors retain any rights not expressly granted under this Agreement.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Term and Termination</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This Agreement will begin when you accept these Terms and Conditions on the University Bureau website. Either Party may terminate it upon 30 days&#39; written notice to the other Party for any reason, without cause.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau has the right to cancel this Agreement immediately and without cause if:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you break this Agreement materially and fail to correct the breach within 30 calendar days of the University Bureau notifying you of the violation; or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>if you violate any of the statements you made in this Agreement; or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If University Bureau is unable to provide any part or all of the University Bureau as a result of (A) your breaches of this Agreement; (B) the acts or omissions of any third party (including any University BureauPartner); or (C) any Applicable Law or ruling issued in any form by a Governmental or Regulatory Authority.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Effect of Termination or Expiry</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; If this Agreement is terminated or expires (whether by you or University Bureau), you shall stop using the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any fees accumulated hereunder or payments payable before the effective date of termination or expiration shall not be affected if this Agreement is terminated or expires for any reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neither Party&#39;s accrued rights or remedies are affected by the termination of this Agreement by either Party.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any part of this Agreement that specifically indicates that it will continue to apply after the termination or expiration of this Agreement or that would survive the termination or expiration of this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Disclaimers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, INCLUDING FOR GREATER CERTAINTY, THE CONTENT, REFERENCES, LINKS, AND INFORMATION IN THE CONTENT, IS PROVIDED TO YOU &ldquo;AS IS&rdquo; WITHOUT WARRANTY OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU HAS NO SPECIAL RELATIONSHIP WITH YOU OR ANY OTHER USER OF THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU. YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THAT THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU HAS NO CONTROL OVER AND NO DUTY TO TAKE ANY ACTION REGARDING ANY ACTS OR OMISSIONS TAKEN BY YOU OR ANY OTHER USER OF THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, INCLUDING HOW YOU OR ANY OTHER USER MAY INTERPRET OR USE CONTENT OBTAINED THROUGH THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, OR WHAT ACTIONS YOU MAY TAKE AS A RESULT OF BEING EXPOSED TO CONTENT OBTAINED THROUGH THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU&#39;S CONTENT CONTAINS REFERENCES TO THIRD PARTIES, INCLUDING THE UNIVERSITY BUREAUPARTNERS, LINKS TO THIRD-PARTY WEBSITES OR DOCUMENTS, AND INFORMATION OBTAINED FROM THIRD PARTIES, INCLUDING THE UNIVERSITY BUREAUPARTNERS. UNIVERSITY BUREAU MAY ALSO CREATE CONTENT BASED ON SUCH THIRD-PARTY INFORMATION, WHICH MAY CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE TO THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU MAY INCLUDE LINKS TO THIRD-PARTY WEBSITES, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTION WEBSITES. THESE LINKS ARE PROVIDED SOLELY FOR YOUR AND THE OTHER USERS OF THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU&#39;S CONVENIENCE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>WE DO NOT ENDORSE OR GUARANTEE THE QUALITY, ACCURACY, RELIABILITY, COMPLETENESS, CURRENCY, TIMELINESS, NON-INFRINGEMENT, MERCHANTABILITY, OR FITNESS FOR ANY PURPOSE OF THE INFORMATION, PRODUCTS, OR SERVICES DESCRIBED ON THOSE WEBSITES. THE CONTENT OF ANY LINKED WEBSITE IS NOT UNDER OUR CONTROL AND DOES NOT FORM PART OF THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, AND ACCESSING ANY SUCH WEBSITE IS AT YOUR OWN RISK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU ASSUMES NO LIABILITY FOR ANY ERRORS, OMISSIONS, INACCURACIES, EFFECTIVENESS, STANDARDS COMPLIANCE, COPYRIGHT COMPLIANCE, LEGALITY, DECENCY, OR ANY OTHER FEATURE OF THE CONTENT PROVIDED THROUGH THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UNIVERSITY BUREAU SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY LOSS OR DAMAGE CAUSED BY YOUR RELIANCE ON CONTENT OBTAINED THROUGH THE USE OF THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, INCLUDING ANY THIRD PARTY LINKED SITE (INCLUDING ANY OPINIONS, STATEMENTS, OR ADVICE).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>YOU ARE SOLELY RESPONSIBLE FOR EVALUATING THE ACCURACY, COMPLETENESS, AND USEFULNESS OF ANY CONTENT PROVIDED, AND YOU ARE USING THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU AT YOUR OWN RISK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CONCERNING THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU&#39;S USE OF YOUR DATA TO PROVIDE THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, UNIVERSITY BUREAU WILL HAVE NO LIABILITY WHATSOEVER TO YOU OR ANY THIRD PARTY WHOSE CONTENT IS COLLECTED IN YOUR USE OF THE UNIVERSITY BUREAU, WHETHER RELATED TO PRIVACY OR OTHERWISE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau has no control over University BureauPartners or any other entity granting visas, admissions, permits, or other authorizations in connection with the Application; you acknowledge that such third parties, not University Bureau, are solely responsible for the success of your Application, and thus release University Bureau from all liability in relation to your application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau is not liable in any manner for your application, data errors, or inability to get admission to your desired program(s) or University BureauPartner (s).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All concerns relating to Applications, Programs, and your failure to follow University BureauPartner policies are entirely between you and the appropriate University Bureau Partner. The University Bureau bears no duty or obligation in such matters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are entirely responsible for complying with Applicable Law and any Governmental or Regulatory Authorities requirements to acquire entrance into the nation where your Program is located.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While University Bureau has made reasonable measures to ensure that its agreements