 computer system and the full cost of any servicing, repairs, or connections to your computer system that may be required as a consequence of your use of the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau cannot guarantee the privacy of any communications you send through the University Bureau, over the Internet, or by phone. Despite the fact that University Bureau generally follows industry best practices in securing data transmission to, from, and through the University Bureau, you understand, agree, and acknowledge that University Bureau cannot and does not guarantee the security of data transmitted over the Internet or public networks in connection with your use of the University Bureau.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Your Concern</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold University Bureau, its officers, directors, employees, and agents, as well as its parent company, subsidiaries, and affiliates, harmless from and against any and all claims, causes of action, demands, recoveries, losses, damages, fines, penalties, or other costs or expenses of any kind or nature, including reasonable legal and accounting fees, arising out of or in connection with:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>your use of the University Bureau, as well as any reliance you place on any Content accessed from the University Bureau; or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>your abuse or illegal use of the University Bureau; or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a violation of this Agreement by you; or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>the infringement, violation, or misappropriation of any intellectual property or other right of a third party by you or any third-party gaining access to the University Bureau using your Access Information; or</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any applicable laws that you have broken.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Limitation of Liability</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To the maximum extent permitted by Applicable Law, University Bureau will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, special, exemplary, or punitive damages, lost profits, loss of use, loss of data, personal injury, fines, fees, penalties, or other liabilities, whether or not University Bureauis advised of the possibility of such damages, resulting from any warranty, contract, tort, negligence, strict liability, or any other legal theory, whether or not University Bureau is advised of the possibility of such damages,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>University Bureau&#39;s total aggregate liability in connection with or under this Agreement, your use of, or inability to use, the University Bureau, or any other claim related in any way to your use of, or inability to use, the University Bureau, will not exceed 1,000 Canadian dollars, to the maximum extent permitted by Applicable Law. The presence of one or more claims under this Agreement will not raise the maximum liability amount, just to be precise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nothing in this Agreement diminishes University Bureau&#39;s responsibility for fraud, bodily damage, or death to the extent that the university Bureau&#39;s carelessness or deliberate misconduct is the cause.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The restrictions in this section are based on the risk distribution between the parties. Even if any limited remedy described in this Agreement is determined to have failed in its basic purpose, the restrictions outlined in this Section will continue and apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BECAUSE SOME JURISDICTIONS DO NOT ALLOW LIMITATIONS OR EXCLUSIONS OF LIABILITY FOR INCIDENTAL OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, THESE LIMITATIONS OR EXCLUSIONS MAY NOT APPLY TO YOU.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Except as expressly stated in this Agreement, the Parties&#39; rights and remedies are cumulative. The phrases &quot;including&quot; and &quot;including&quot; indicate &quot;without restriction&quot; and &quot;including without limitation,&quot; respectively. The section headers are for reference only and have no legal significance. Any rule of construction that any ambiguity in this Agreement will be resolved against the writing party will not be applied to this Agreement&#39;s interpretation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neither Party shall be responsible for delays caused by events beyond its reasonable control, except that this condition will not excuse non-payment of monies due under this Agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nothing in this Agreement shall be considered to form or suggest a joint venture, partnership, principal-agent, or employment relationship between the Parties. You will not act or claim to act as University Bureau&#39;s legal agent, enter into any arrangement on behalf of University Bureau, or otherwise bind or purport to bind University Bureau unless University Bureau expressly authorizes you to do so in writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any notices, reports, or other communications required or permitted to be given under this Agreement must be in writing, including by email. They must be delivered by hand or sent by registered mail, courier, or facsimile to you or the University Bureau at the respective addresses as advised in writing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any such notices, reports, or other communications will be deemed received by the Party to whom they were addressed: I upon delivery by hand, (ii) five business days after being sent by registered mail, (iii) upon delivery by courier, as evidenced by the courier receipt, (iv) upon successful receipt confirmation report after being sent by facsimile, or (v) upon receipt by the sender of a delivery receipt confirmation if sent by email.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unless explicitly given in writing and signed by the waiving Party, no waiver by either Party of a breach or omission by the other under this Agreement will influence the waiving Party. A Party&#39;s waiver of a specific breach or omission by the other Party has no bearing on or affects the waiving party&#39;s rights in a later breach or deletion of the same or different sort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose any term of this Agreement is invalid, unlawful, or unenforceable. In that case, that provision will be severable from the rest of the Agreement, and the remainder of the Agreement will be treated as if that provision had never been.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The laws of the Province of Ontario, Canada, will govern and construe this Agreement. The Parties expressly waive any right to a jury trial about any litigation or judicial procedure originating or pertaining to this Agreement. Choice of law principles will not be applied in construing, interpreting, or enforcing this Agreement. The University Bureau is only intended to be used in places where it is legal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recruiter hereby consents to the exclusive jurisdiction and venue of the courts in Toronto, Ontario, Canada, in any matters arising out of or about the use of the University Bureau, unless as prohibited by Applicable Law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This Agreement contains the Parties&#39; full agreement and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings about the subject matter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You understand and agree that you are entering into a legally binding contract by clicking on the &quot;I AGREE&quot; button (or similar buttons or links as may be designated by the University Bureau to signify your acceptance of this Consent and your agreement to use the University Bureau). You agree to utilize electronic communication to enter into contracts, place orders, establish other records, and receive notices, policies, and descriptions of transactions begun or completed through the University Bureau, including the Application,